President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. Jeffery Martin Baran of Virginia is nominated to be a Member of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission, Michael T. Evanoff of Arkansas is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of State, Diplomatic Security, Andrei Iancu of California is nominated to be Under Secretary of Commerce for Intellectual Property and Director of the United States Patent and Trademark Office, and Adam I. Klein of the District of Columbia is nominated to be a Member and Chairman of the Privacy & Civil Liberties Oversight Board.